  ## Summary                                                                  
                                                                              
  I've added a new EFO term for the **TeloHAEC cell line** as requested in    
  GitHub issue #2344.                                                         
                                                                              
  ### Changes Made                                                            
                                                                              
  **File**: src/ontology/efo-edit.owl                                         
                                                                              
  Added new term **EFO_****0920063** with:                                    
                                                                              
  • **Label**: TeloHAEC                                                       
  • **Definition**: An hTERT-immortalized cell line derived from human        
  thoracic aorta.                                                             
  • **Parent term**: EFO:0005730 (endothelial cell derived cell line) -       
  directly requested in the issue                                             
  • **Logical definition**: Following the same pattern as BAEC (EFO_0022822,  
  bovine aortic endothelial cell line), but using NCBITaxon_9606 (Homo        
  sapiens) instead of NCBITaxon_9913 (bovine). This allows the reasoner to    
  infer EFO:0002888 (Homo sapiens cell line) as a classification.             
  • **Cross-reference**: RRID:CVCL_Z065 (Cellosaurus entry)                   
  • **Definition PMIDs**:                                                     
      • PMID:32155782 (Marqués et al., 2020 - Cells) - uses TeloHAEC cells,   
      describes them as "a clonal line immortalized by stably expressing hTERT
      (from human telomerase)" available from ATCC                            
      • PMID:39456453 (Marqués et al., 2024 - Antioxidants) - uses TeloHAEC in
      aortic endothelial research                                             
  • **seeAlso**: https://github.com/EBISPOT/efo/issues/2344

